{
  "texts": [
    "This leads to the following conjecture of [CGV25].",
    "Conjecture 2.1 (Conjecture 1.4 in [CGV25]).",
    "Let G = (V, E) be a connected graph, with (v 1, v 2) / ∈ E, and such that for any partition of V in ℓ groups, with v 1, v 2 in the same group, the number",
    "with r:= |E|/(|V | -2).",
    "Then, if q ≍ n -1/r and λ ≥ log q 1-log n (K), we can recover the communities in the SBM with an algorithm based on P G, counting of the occurrence of the motif G."
  ]
}